<?xml version="1.0"?>
<h:html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2002/xforms" xmlns:h="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:ev="http://www.w3.org/2001/xml-events" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:jr="http://openrosa.org/javarosa" xmlns:orx="http://openrosa.org/xforms" xmlns:odk="http://www.opendatakit.org/xforms" xmlns:cht="https://communityhealthtoolkit.org">
  <h:head>
    <h:title>Android App Launcher</h:title>
    <model odk:xforms-version="1.0.0">
      <itext>
        <translation lang="English (en)">
          <text id="/data/intro:label">
            <value>This form demonstrates how to accept form input from other Android apps. See the [CHT Docs](https://docs.communityhealthtoolkit.org/apps/reference/forms/app/#android-app-launcher) for more information.</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/data/intro:hint">
            <value>Note that to use this form, you must be running an instance of cht-android with the `READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE` permission enabled and you must have the [com.atharok.barcodescanner](https://gitlab.com/Atharok/BarcodeScanner) app installed.</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/data/camera_image:label">
            <value>Capturing an image from the camera</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/data/camera_image/camera_app/camera_app_outputs/data:label">
            <value>Tap the button to use the camera app on your device to take a picture.</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/data/camera_image/camera_app/camera_app_outputs/data:hint">
            <value>Using the `display-base64-image` appearance allows for displaying the image from the camera in the form.</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/data/qr_code:label">
            <value>Capturing data from a QR code</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/data/qr_code/qr_code_app/qr_code_app_outputs/SCAN_RESULT:label">
            <value>Tap the button to use the Barcode Scanner app on your device to scan a barcode value.</value>
          </text>
          <text id="/data/qr_code/qr_code_app/qr_code_app_outputs/SCAN_RESULT:hint">
            <value>A great way to test this on an emulated device is to use the com.atharok.barcodescanner app to create a new QR code image and save that image to the device. Then, when the form launches the app again to scan a QR code, you can load the saved QR code image instead of needing to "scan" a QR code with the emulated camera.</value>
          </text>
        </translation>
      </itext>
      <instance>
        <data id="android_app_launcher" version="20260114091903" prefix="J1!android_app_launcher!" delimiter="#">
          <intro/>
          <camera_image>
            <camera_app>
              <action>android.media.action.IMAGE_CAPTURE</action>
              <camera_app_outputs>
                <data/>
              </camera_app_outputs>
            </camera_app>
          </camera_image>
          <qr_code>
            <qr_code_app>
              <action>com.google.zxing.client.android.SCAN</action>
              <qr_code_app_outputs>
                <SCAN_RESULT/>
              </qr_code_app_outputs>
            </qr_code_app>
          </qr_code>
          <meta tag="hidden">
            <instanceID/>
          </meta>
        </data>
      </instance>
      <instance id="contact-summary"/>
      <instance id="user-contact-summary"/>
      <bind nodeset="/data/intro" readonly="true()" type="string"/>
      <bind nodeset="/data/camera_image/camera_app/action" type="string"/>
      <bind nodeset="/data/camera_image/camera_app/camera_app_outputs/data" type="string"/>
      <bind nodeset="/data/qr_code/qr_code_app/action" type="string"/>
      <bind nodeset="/data/qr_code/qr_code_app/qr_code_app_outputs/SCAN_RESULT" type="string" calculate="coalesce(., &quot;&quot;)" readonly="true()"/>
      <bind nodeset="/data/meta/instanceID" type="string" readonly="true()" jr:preload="uid"/>
    </model>
  </h:head>
  <h:body class="pages">
    <input ref="/data/intro">
      <label ref="jr:itext('/data/intro:label')"/>
      <hint ref="jr:itext('/data/intro:hint')"/>
    </input>
    <group appearance="field-list" ref="/data/camera_image">
      <label ref="jr:itext('/data/camera_image:label')"/>
      <group appearance="android-app-launcher" ref="/data/camera_image/camera_app">
        <group appearance="android-app-outputs" ref="/data/camera_image/camera_app/camera_app_outputs">
          <input ref="/data/camera_image/camera_app/camera_app_outputs/data" appearance="display-base64-image">
            <label ref="jr:itext('/data/camera_image/camera_app/camera_app_outputs/data:label')"/>
            <hint ref="jr:itext('/data/camera_image/camera_app/camera_app_outputs/data:hint')"/>
          </input>
        </group>
      </group>
    </group>
    <group appearance="field-list" ref="/data/qr_code">
      <label ref="jr:itext('/data/qr_code:label')"/>
      <group appearance="android-app-launcher" ref="/data/qr_code/qr_code_app">
        <group appearance="android-app-outputs" ref="/data/qr_code/qr_code_app/qr_code_app_outputs">
          <input ref="/data/qr_code/qr_code_app/qr_code_app_outputs/SCAN_RESULT">
            <label ref="jr:itext('/data/qr_code/qr_code_app/qr_code_app_outputs/SCAN_RESULT:label')"/>
            <hint ref="jr:itext('/data/qr_code/qr_code_app/qr_code_app_outputs/SCAN_RESULT:hint')"/>
          </input>
        </group>
      </group>
    </group>
  </h:body>
</h:html>